Anyway, earlier this week we were there.  Normally, I chant the mob down to about 80%, then she's free to load it up with dots and/or nuke to her hearts content.  Now if she does ANYTHING to the mob prior to me chanting it to about 70% the mob immediately runs for her.  <br>
This week was the first time we'd done serious chant kiting in HoH for awhile, but we didn't notice a problem in LDoNs (I tank when we each 2 box) until after the recent string of patches.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=racket@theconcerthall>Racket</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 866<br> <font color=#330000>(7/23/04 8:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19624.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reduced aggro on chants</span><hr size=1> Yea the agro on chants has been greatly reduced.  Kinda sucks for trying none standard groups with no tank.<br>
